7c8d9e0f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c0d1e2f3a4b5c6d7e8f9a0b1c2d3e4f5a6b7c8d9e0f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c0d1e2f3a4b5c6d7e8f9a0b1c2d3e4f5a6
Civil Plan Proposal. 001.DET.2026
To. The Office of the Mayor. City of Detroit
From. Continuity Collective, LLC
Subject. The Detroit Regeneration Initiative. A "closed loop" logistics framework for emergency housing and urban reforestation.
1. Executive Summary
This document outlines a zero waste civil infrastructure plan designed to address two critical municipal failures simultaneously. (1) The humanitarian crisis of winter homelessness and (2) the ecological blight of vacant urban land. By utilizing the "Love Core" logistic framework. we propose a public private partnership that transforms waste streams (corrugated cardboard) into life saving thermal shelters that eventually decompose into fertile soil for reforestation.
2. Phase I. The "Winter Shield" Protocol (Emergency Housing)
 * Objective. Zero freezing deaths in the 2026/2027 winter season.
 * The Structure. The "Hexi Dome" system. A geodesic emergency unit constructed from recovered corrugated board.
 * Material Science. Units are coated in a proprietary "Bio Armor" consisting of locally sourced Michigan Blue Clay (binder). Gluten/Egg Protein (hardener). and Aerosolized Mica (insulator/waterproofer).
 * Deployment. Units are "flat packed" and palletized for rapid deployment by DPD Neighborhood Police Officers (NPO) and municipal crews.
 * Engineering. The hexagonal geometry sheds wind loads up to 75 mph. The clay/mica shell provides thermal mass. retaining heat from small electric sources or body warmth.
3. Phase II. Resource Diversion & Logistics
 * The Amazon Stream. The City will partner with major logistics carriers to divert clean cardboard waste directly to "Neighborhood Manufacturing Hubs" rather than distant pulping centers. This eliminates tipping fees.
 * The Big 3 Stewardship. We call upon Ford. GM. and Stellantis to provide the logistical fleet for the distribution of flat packs. Utilizing the "Engine of Community." these fleets will ensure that shelter reaches the "No Man's Land" sectors of the city efficiently.
 * Labor Force. The "Green Corps." A jobs program employing at risk youth and former shelter residents to operate the "Spray Teams." utilizing the texture hopper guns to seal the units on site.
4. Phase III. Ecological Succession (The Spring Protocol)
 * Lifecycle Management. These units are designed as "Single Season" infrastructure. They are not intended to be permanent slums but temporary cocoons.
 * Decomposition. Upon the spring thaw (April/May). the units are vacated. The spring rains soften the clay and pulp the cardboard.
 * Reforestation. The breakdown process creates a nitrogen rich mulch mound (perfect Carbon/Nitrogen ratio).
 * Action. Municipal forestry crews will plant native saplings (Oak. Maple. Fruit) directly into the center of the collapsing shelter.
 * Outcome. What began as a homeless camp in December becomes a young urban forest in June. The "waste" becomes the nursery for the city's green future.
5. Budgetary Impact
 * Cost Reduction. Traditional shelter construction is high capital. This proposal utilizes negative cost materials (waste stream) and low cost local minerals (clay).
 * Health Savings. drastic reduction in emergency room visits for frostbite and hypothermia among the unhoused population.
6. Conclusion
Detroit has the land. Detroit has the clay. Detroit has the heart. This plan moves us from "managing homelessness" to "engineering hope." It is a solution that respects the dignity of the human spirit and the cycles of the earth.
Submitted By.
Kenneth L. Cooper
"Lion of Light"
Continuity Collective, LLC
End Thread
